  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3222",
  "title": "when using searchFunction hook my pagination stops working",
  "body": "I'm running into a problem with `searchFunction` not respecting the pagination. When I create my instantsearch object I pass in \r\n\r\n```\r\n            searchFunction: function (helper) {\r\n               // helper.getPage() == correct page\r\n                var query = helper.getQuery().query;\r\n                if (query === '') {\r\n                    // for blank search (starting) everything within 50 is valued the same on geo.\r\n                    helper.setQueryParameter('aroundPrecision', 50 * metersInMile);\r\n                } else {\r\n                    // when a search term is added anything within 500 miles is valued the same on geo.\r\n                    helper.setQueryParameter('aroundPrecision', 500 * metersInMile);\r\n                }\r\n                // helper.getPage() == 0\r\n                helper.search();\r\n            },\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe pagination widget doesn't paginate the results.\r\n```\r\n            instantsearch.widgets.pagination({\r\n                container: '#pagination-top',\r\n                maxPages: 50,\r\n                // default is to scroll to 'body', here we disable this behavior\r\n                scrollTo: false\r\n            })\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I remove `searchFunction` it will start working again. I'm wondering if I have to set all the parameters (search term, pagination page) if I use `setQueryParameter` once. If that is the case does that mean helper loses all incoming options when `setQueryParameter` is called?",
